# Secrets — never bake a real .env into an image layer via `docker build`.
# Note this is a build-context guarantee only: `docker-compose up`'s bind
# mount (docker-compose.yml) gives the running container direct access to
# whatever's actually in the host repo, including a real .env if one exists
# there — that's intentional, and matches how this project already reads
# .env for non-Docker local dev (config/settings.py).
.env*
!.env.example

# Local SQLite database and its WAL journal siblings.
db.sqlite3
db.sqlite3-wal
db.sqlite3-shm

# Python artifacts.
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# VCS / tooling / pipeline artifacts not needed at runtime.
.git/
.claude/
plan/
.playwright-mcp/
backlog.md
claude-edits.log
WORKFLOW_STATE.md
